Members of Parliament debate President Cyril Ramaphosa's State of the Nation Address. Courtesy #DStv403 CAPE TOWN - Opposition parties fired their first shots against President Cyril Ramaphosa's state of the nation address. Members of Parliament gathered in the Cape Town City Hall on Monday to debate the president's take on the country's priorities. READ: MPs debate 2022 State of the Nation Address While the DA has accused Ramaphosa of inaction, the party has already filed a motion of no confidence against the entire executive.